2. Difference between Canvas App and Model-Driven App?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1ï¸âƒ£ Canvas Apps:
ğŸ‘‰ Canvas gives full control over the app layouts and UI from scratch, adding different elements like buttons,galleries,forms, etc.
ğŸ‘‰ We can start with a blank screen and design the app using a drag-and-drop components, (Use Power Fx formulas to handle logic).
ğŸ‘‰ we can Connect to multiple data sources like SharePoint, Excel, SQL, Dataverse, etc.

2ï¸âƒ£ Model-Driven Apps:
ğŸ‘‰ Model-Driven Apps are best for complex scenarios with structured data in Dataverse.
ğŸ‘‰ User Interface(UI) is automatically generated based on data models stored in Dataverse.
ğŸ‘‰ We can create forms, views, tables, that are automated generated based on the data entities adn relationships.

âœ… â€œIn short, Canvas = full design control, Model-Driven = full data structure control.â€
