3. Variables and types of Variables in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Variables are used to store and manage data temporarily while app is running.
ğŸ‘‰ It allows me to hold values like type numbers, text strings, boolean, record, table..etc.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Variables in Power Apps:
1. Global Variables (Set):
ğŸ‘‰ Used anywhere in the app, across all screens. Created using the Set() function.
âœ… Syntax: Set(varCountry, "india") ----- Set(varName,"value")

2. Context Variables (UpdateContext):
ğŸ‘‰ Only available on the current screen. Created with UpdateContext() function.
âœ… Syntax: UpdateContext({ varName: "Manoj" })
