4. Collections and types of Collections in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Collections is a group of items or i can say group of infomation that you can create, edit, and use inside your app.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Collections in Power Apps:
1. Collect() Function:
ğŸ‘‰ The Collect() function is used to create a new collection or add records to an existing collection.
âœ… Syntax: Collect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice", Age: 25}) ------ {Name:TextInput.text, Age:Value(TextInput.text)}

2. ClearCollect() Function:
ğŸ‘‰ The ClearCollect() Function is used to remove all the existing records from collection, it allows me add a new record.
âœ… Syntax: ClearCollect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice1", Age: 20})

3. Clear() Function:
ğŸ‘‰ The Clear() function is used to remove all records (rows) from a collection.
âœ… Syntax: Clear(MyCollection)
